quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  2,106,"If We abrogate a verse or cause it to be forgotten, We will replace it by a better one or one similar to it. Do you not know that God has power over all things"
  2,107,Do you not know that the kingdom of the heavens and the earth belongs to God alone? And that there is no protector or helper for you besides God
  2,108,"Do you [all] want to question your messenger just as Moses was questioned previously? Anyone who exchanges faith for unbelief has strayed from the right path"
  2,109,"Many among the People of the Book wish, through envy, to lead you back to unbelief, now that you have embraced the faith and the truth has been made plain to them. But you should pardon them and bear with them until God gives His command. Truly, God has power over all things"
  2,110,"Attend to your prayers and pay the prescribed alms; any good you store up for yourselves, you will find it with God. Certainly, God sees what you do"
  2,111,"They declare, \"None shall ever enter Heaven unless he be a Jew or a Christian.\" This is their own wishful thinking. [Prophet], say, \"Produce your evidence if you are telling the truth"
  2,112,"Indeed, those who submit themselves to God and act righteously shall be rewarded by their Lord: they shall have no fear, nor shall they grieve"